claim.claim-text:
10. A composite package comprising:
a first panel defining a first opening;
a second panel joined to said first panel by a hinge and rotatable with respect to said first panel about said hinge;
a first plastic component with a first pocket and a first flange, said first flange joined to said first panel;
a second plastic component with a second flange joined to said second panel, said first and second plastic components being integrally joined to each other along a portion of said first flange and a portion of said second flange; and
wherein said first panel and second panel can be selectively moved about said hinge between a closed position in which said first panel and said second panel are adjacent to one another and a portion of said first plastic component releasably interlocks with a portion of said second plastic component by frictional interfit to cooperatively define an interior space and an open position in which said first panel is hinged away from said second panel and said first plastic component is hinged away from said second plastic component to provide access to said interior space, wherein said first and second panels can be repeatedly moved between said closed position and said open position without damaging the package,
wherein said first and second flanges each have an inside surface facing toward each other when said first and second panels are in said closed position, and an outside surface facing away from each other when said first and second panels are in said closed position, wherein said first panel is positioned adjacent said outside surface of said first flange and said second panel is positioned adjacent said outside surface of said second flange,
wherein said first panel remains joined to said first flange and said second panel remains joined to said second flange as said paperboard panel repeatedly moves between said closed and said open positions, and said first and second plastic components engage one another when said hinge of said paperboard orients said first and second panels in said closed position and said first and second plastic components are separated when said hinge of said paperboard orients said first and second panels in said open position.
